in.ac.iitk.cse.putwb.experiment

Class PUTExperiment

  • java.lang.Object
    • in.ac.iitk.cse.putwb.experiment.PUTExperiment
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Verifier

    public class PUTExperiment
extends Object
    This class represents a particular Privacy-Utility tradeoff experiment. It involves providing a dataset, setting a number of parameters, running the learning tasks, collecting stats and saving them in an output file.
    The usage details can be known by running the class, without any parameters.
    Author:
    Saurabh Srivastava

        public void resumeExperimentAfterGenerationStage(Set<Set<Integer>> partitions,

      • resumeExperimentFromGenerationStage

        public void resumeExperimentFromGenerationStage(int numberOfCombinationsToGenerate,
                                                Set<Set<Integer>> recoveredPartitions,
                                                boolean isRandomlyGenerated)
        Resumes the current experiment from the partition generation stage. If the partitions were generated via random generation method, any partitions that were recovered can be reused.
        Parameters:
        numberOfCombinationsToGenerate - The total number of partitions that are supposed to be generated
        recoveredPartitions - The set of partitions recovered from the recovery file
        isRandomlyGenerated - If true, signifies that the partitions were generated in random order, false signifies that the partitions were generated in dictionary order

      • runCompatibilityTests

        public String runCompatibilityTests()
        Runs a set of compatibility tests to check current experiment configurations.
        This method can be used to perform any checks over the dataset and parameters, before starting the experiment.
        The method is not invoked implicitly, and must be called explicitly before starting the experiment. Currently the following tests are performed in the method:
        1. Check if the dataset's class attribute is set or not.
        2. Check if the class attribute is nominal or not.
        3. Check that the number of attribute combinations to generate (without privacy exceptions) is not larger than the maximum value of integer - Integer.MAX_VALUE
        4. If the selected Classifier is SGD, the dataset must not have more than two classes.
        Returns:
        An error message and/or warning indicating a problem (the first one detected in the sequence), null if no problems occurred while running the tests
